        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued July 20 at 10:18PM MDT until July 20 at 10:45PM MDT by NWS Billings MT</headline>
        <description>At 1018 PM MDT, Severe thunderstorms were located along a line from
16 miles east of Ekalaka to 15 miles southeast of Ridgeway, or along
a line from 16 miles east of Ekalaka to 42 miles south of Ekalaka,
moving east at 55 mph.

HAZARD...Ping pong ball size hail and 60 mph wind gusts.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...People and animals outdoors will be injured. Expect hail
damage to roofs, siding, windows, and vehicles. Expect
wind damage to roofs, siding, and trees.

Locations impacted include...
Ekalaka, Ridgeway, Belltower, Mill Iron, Capitol, Albion and
Medicine Rocks State Park.
</description>
        <instruction>Seek shelter inside a well-built structure and stay away from
windows. These storms are capable of producing damaging winds and
large hail.</instruction>
